			<h3>Anycast</h3>
			<p>Anycast routes outbound traffic to the nearest or best available node among multiple nodes advertising the same address — commonly used for DNS, CDNs, and resilient network services.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "geo-alt" %}</span>
			<h3>Geocast</h3>
			<p>Geocast routes outbound traffic to nodes within a specific geographic area, helping deliver ultra-low-latency, high-quality voice by keeping media paths local and efficient.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "diagram-3" %}</span>
			<h3>Diverse Routing</h3>
			<p>Diverse inbound routing tests multiple network paths or carriers, automatically selecting the best route and maintaining stability to the last hop.</p>
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

